{
  "texts": [
    "Initial evaluation suggested that the combined rating items had a Cronbach's alpha score of.81.",
    "Further factor analysis (reported in SM) suggested that one factor may be most suitable to capture the four items.",
    "However, given that this was the first investigation of these items, we decided to report each outcome separately EXPLORING HUMAN AND AI EMOTIONAL SUPPORT to further examine whether the difference between GPT-4 and human is more pronounced in some measures (Figure 1).",
    "We found that, averaged over the emotion categories, GPT reappraisals were rated significantly higher than human reappraisals in terms of effectiveness, (b = -0.59, t(178)= -3.06, p =.003, 95% CI [-0.97,-0.21]), empathy (b =-0.60, t(172)=-3.34,p=.001, 95% CI [-0.95,-0.25]), and novelty (b = -0.27, t(153)= -2.51, p =.013, 95% CI [-0.47,-0.06]).",
    "We did not, however, see a difference between GPT reappraisals and human reappraisals in terms of specificity (b = -0.09, t(138) = -1.20, p=.233, 95% CI [-0.23,0.06]) suggesting that GPT produced reappraisals were not more specifically related to the vignette compared to the human produced reappraisals."
  ]
}